article.headline: Old Dominion 87, N.C.-Wilmington 57
article.story: NORFOLK, Va. -- Marsharee Neely scored a career-high 20 points to lead four Old Dominion players in double figures as the Monarchs routed North Carolina-Wilmington 87-57 on Wednesday night. Old Dominion (11-7, 4-4 Colonial Athletic Association) scored 38 points off 21 Seahawks turnovers. The Monarchs never trailed and led 46-29 at halftime. Old Dominion led by as many as 36 points at 74-38 with 10:01 left and shot 57.1 percent for the game (36 of 63). UNC-Wilmington (4-16, 1-7) has lost three straight, and failed to reach 60 points in its last five losses. The Seahawks were also outrebounded 38-26. Neely shot 7 of 8 from the floor, including 4 of 5 from 3-point range. Ben Finney added 14 points for Old Dominion, and Kent Bazemore and Kevon Carter scored 11 apiece. Dominique Lacy was the only Seahawks player in double figures with 14 points.
